<h3>Law</h3>
<table border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align:top;"><img style="float:left; margin-right:5px;" src="/assets/548/kuguanlogo_normal.jpg" alt="Ku Guan" /></td>
<td><a href="http://law.sjtu.edu.cn/En/">KoGuan Law School</a> has a total number of about 750 law students. Each year we attract many talented applicants throughout China. Our student body is among the best in China in terms of their performance in national entrance exams. In Fall 2010, we launched the first Master of Laws (LL.M.) Program in Chinese Law in Shanghai. This will diversify and internationalize our student body. We welcome international graduate students to join in our Law School. Currently we offer the following English programs:              
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li><a href="http://law.sjtu.edu.cn/International/Article120111.aspx" target="_blank">SJD in Law</a></li>
<li><a href="http://law.sjtu.edu.cn/International/Article120102.aspx" target="_blank">LL.M. in Chinese Law</a></li>
<li><a href="http://law.sjtu.edu.cn/International/Article120401.aspx" target="_blank">Summer Programs</a></li>
<li><a href="http://law.sjtu.edu.cn/International/Article120501.aspx" target="_blank">Visiting Scholars &amp; Students</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h3>International and Public Affairs (SIPA)</h3>
<p>As an internationally-oriented school, <a href="http://www.sipa.sjtu.edu.cn/portal.php?mod=list&amp;catid=133">SIPA</a> has established substantial strategic partnerships with renowned universities around the world, and has a rich and extensive overseas network. To facilitate faculty and student exchanges as well as academic collaboration, the school has signed agreements or memorandums with schools such as Columbia University&rsquo;s School of International and Public Affairs, the Rand Corporation and its Pardee Graduate School, the Moscow State Institute of International Relations (MGIMO), Science Po in Paris, and the University of Bergen&rsquo;s Department of Comparative Politics. Currently, several dozen foreign students are pursuing their degrees at SIPA. Each year, SIPA also selects students to study in America, Europe, Taiwan, and Hong Kong among other locations. We currently offer the following English Program:</p>
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> <a href="http://www.sipa.sjtu.edu.cn/portal.php?mod=view&amp;aid=743">International Master Degree Program of China's Politics and Economy</a> 
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.sipa.sjtu.edu.cn/portal.php?mod=attachment&amp;id=477">Scholarship Info</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.sipa.sjtu.edu.cn/portal.php?mod=attachment&amp;id=483">Team for International Master Degree Program</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.sipa.sjtu.edu.cn/portal.php?mod=attachment&amp;id=475">Course Description</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3>Zhiyuan College</h3>
<p><a title="Zhiyuan College" href="http://zhiyuan.sjtu.edu.cn/default.aspx" target="_blank">Zhiyuan College</a>, founded in January 2010, serves as a fundamental teaching unit at <a title="SJTU" href="/">Shanghai Jiao Tong University (SJTU)</a> to prepare individuals to be leaders and practitioners in basic sciences and related scientific fields.</p>
<p>From 2011, Zhiyuan College began to offer <a title="Programs" href="http://zhiyuan.sjtu.edu.cn/CultivateProject.aspx" target="_blank">four undergraduate programs</a> : Mathematics, Physics, Life Sciences, and Computer Sciences. The curricula of the four programs are designed according to the world leading development of science and technology.</p>
<p>The mission of Zhiyuan College is to foster the ability of our students to raise quality, thought-provoking questions, solve complex problems, promote critical thinking and innovation, and help deepen interpersonal communication through collaboration.</p>
<p>To accomplish this mission, Zhiyuan College formed an oversight committee of teaching, consisting of <a title="world-class faculty member" href="http://zhiyuan.sjtu.edu.cn/Professors.aspx?Index=1" target="_blank">world-class faculty members</a> who excel in both research and teaching. In addition to quality faculty, Zhiyuan offers a series of seminars guided by top scholars invited from around the world. The seminars help guide students on their areas of research. At Zhiyuan, students have numerous opportunities to participate in research with other top universities.</p>
<p>Considering the importance of Zhiyuan College, <a title="President Zhang Jie" href="/about-sjtu/administration/zhang-jie">the President of SJTU, Mr. Jie ZHANG</a>, serves as the Dean of Zhiyuan College. The college is supported by the professional staff who focus on promoting holistic development of students. <a title="Institute of Natural Science" href="http://ins.sjtu.edu.cn/index.php?lang=en&amp;option=com_content&amp;Itemid=1" target="_blank">The Institute of Natural Sciences</a> at SJTU contributes to the academic development of undergraduate students in the Zhiyuan College. In addition, the college has established close collaboration with the departments of <a title="Department of Mathematics" href="http://math.sjtu.edu.cn/index.shtm" target="_blank">Mathematics</a>, <a title="Physics" href="http://en.physics.sjtu.edu.cn/" target="_blank">Physics</a>, <a title="School of Life Science" href="http://life.sjtu.edu.cn/english/" target="_blank">School of Life Sciences</a>, <a title="school of electric, information and electrical engineering" href="http://english.seiee.sjtu.edu.cn/" target="_blank">School of Electronic, Information and Electrical Engineering</a>, <a title="Institute of Med-X" href="http://med-x.sjtu.edu.cn/english/" target="_blank">Institute of Med-X</a>, and <a title="School of Humanities" href="http://shss.sjtu.edu.cn/Shss/index.jsp" target="_blank">School of Humanities</a>. SJTU will spare nothing in promoting the development of Zhiyuan College.</p>
<p>Currently we offer the following courses in English:</p>
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li><a href="http://zhiyuan.sjtu.edu.cn/Course/mathcs2012.htm" target="_blank">Mathematics in Computer Science</a> (<a href="http://202.121.182.13:8080/video/index.php?vdir=..%2Fimages%2Fvideos%2FMathematics+in+Computer+Science+%28Summer+semester%2C+2012%29" target="_blank">Class Video</a>)<br /> -- Instructed by Turing Award Winner John E. Hopcroft </li>
<li><a title="Condensed Matter Physics" href="/assets/1744/Condensed%20Matter%20Physics2012.pdf">Condensed Matter Physics 2012</a></li>
</ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
